//experinces
With 3 plus years of experience in Java, Spring Boot, and microservices, you can target the following positions:

Java Developer (Mid-Level): Many companies look for developers with experience in Spring Boot and microservices for building scalable applications.

Backend Developer: This role focuses on server-side development, and your experience with Spring Boot and microservices would be highly relevant.

Microservices Developer: Since you have direct experience with microservices, you can apply for specialized microservices development roles.

Full-Stack Developer (with Backend Focus): If you have any frontend experience or are willing to learn, some positions look for full-stack developers with backend expertise in Java.

DevOps Engineer (Developer Focused): If you've worked on deployment or infrastructure automation alongside microservices, a DevOps position might be a good fit.

Software Engineer: Many companies use this general title for engineers with experience in frameworks like Spring Boot and microservices.

Consider roles in companies focusing on distributed systems, cloud-native development, or digital transformation, as your microservices expertise will be in demand.



